sentences: Niilo Sevänen (born 19 August 1979) is a musician from Joensuu, Finland.
In 1994, he began learning the bass guitar and formed his first band: a punk rock act called Paise.
The following year, the band changed its name to Stonecrow and began to shift its musical style.
Sevänen left the band two years later due to musical differences.
It is speculated that he did the vocals for Belzebubs' album "Pantheon Of The Nightside Gods".
